<HEADLINE>
<P>
MELVYN HELSTIEN; EMERITUS PROFESSOR OF THEATER AT UCLA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Melvyn Helstien, 70, emeritus professor of theater at UCLA and a puppeteer 
whose research involved the leather puppets of South Asia, where he traveled to 
collect artifacts and other historical information. 
</P>
<P>
He was an internationally recognized expert in his field and served as head of 
the U.S. branch of the Union Internationale de la Marrionette. Over the years 
he taught theater, children's theater and stage direction while also producing 
puppet shows both on and off the UCLA campus. Some of his creations have been 
displayed at the Museum of the City of New York and in other prestigious art 
centers around the country. In West Los Angeles on March 6 of the complications 
of a stroke. 
</P>
</TEXT>
