<HEADLINE>
<P>
MALATHION SPRAYING FOR THE PESKY MEDFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
It seems abundantly clear that a large number of citizens do not approve of the 
aerial spraying of malathion upon our communities. 
</P>
<P>
Yet our state government seems, at best, sluggish and aloof in its response to 
citizen concerns regarding this issue. My question is this: From where does the 
power of government stem? Based upon the experience of this ongoing malathion 
saga, the power of government obviously does not reside with us ordinary 
citizens. 
</P>
<P>
The implications brought forth in this struggle go far beyond the pros and cons 
of malathion -- what might be suggested is an implementation of basic 
democratic reforms in this country. 
</P>
<P>
BEN MILES 
</P>
<P>
Huntington Beach 
