<P>
CYPRESS TOPS CERRITOS; PICKLER GETS 100TH VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Cypress softball Coach Brad Pickler got his 100th career victory when the 
Chargers defeated Cerritos, 1-0, in eight innings in the first game of pool 
play in the Golden West softball tournament Friday at Golden West. 
</P>
<P>
Pickler then improved his record to 101-52 when the Chargers defeated College 
of the Sequoias, 4-0, in another game Friday. 
</P>
<P>
Laura Corson (9-1) pitched a two-hitter for Cypress in the first game. Kerry 
Callahan had two hits and an RBI in the second game for Cypress (18-2). Sally 
Dugas (9-1) allowed four hits for the victory. 
</P>
<P>
In other Golden West tournament games: 
</P>
<P>
Golden West 8, El Camino 6 (9 innings) -- El Camino rallied for three runs in 
the bottom of the seventh to tie it, 3-3, and force extra innings. Golden West 
scored five runs in the ninth and then hung on. Dana Cipollone had three hits, 
Jyll Pattinson had two hits and two RBIs and Gretchen Bock had two hits for 
Golden West (17-8). Tara Snyder had a two-run single to cap the ninth-inning 
rally for Golden West. Lisa Kaufman (9-5), despite allowing three runs in both 
the seventh and ninth innings, got the victory. 
</P>
<P>
Golden West 8, Kings River 1 -- Lisa Kaufman pitched a three-hitter in a 
five-inning game called because of a time limit. Dana Cipollone had two hits 
and an RBI in the fifth when Golden West scored eight times. 
</P>
<P>
Orange Coast 7, San Joaquin Delta 3 -- Kim Clark and Nancy Johnson each had two 
hits and scored two runs for OCC. Niqua Monson (4-2) pitched seven innings for 
the victory. 
</P>
<P>
Palomar 5, Orange Coast 0 -- Orange Coast was held to two hits and fell to 
15-4. Palomar, the defending state champion, is 20-3. 
</P>
