<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY EARNINGS: DATUM INC. REPORTS 25% INCREASE IN PROFITS FOR 1989 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Anaheim-based Datum Inc. said net earnings for 1989 rose 25% to $1.4 million 
from $1.1 million in 1988. 
</P>
<P>
The 1988 figure included a $103,000 extraordinary gain from an accounting 
change. Revenue reached a record $37 million, up 16% from the $31.9 million 
posted a year earlier. The results include the first full year of operations 
from Austron Inc., which was acquired in 1988. 
</P>
<P>
For the fourth quarter, net income totaled $370,000, compared to $83,000 for 
the comparable 1988 quarter. Revenue rose 12% to $9.8 million from $8.8 
million. 
</P>
<P>
Datum manufactures precision frequency products and timing instrumentation for 
military, industrial, space and commercial applications. 
</P>
</TEXT>
