<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bergen Brunswig Corp.: The Orange-based distributor of prescription drugs, 
health care products and prerecorded videocassettes reported that net earnings 
for its second fiscal quarter reached a record $15.4 million, 34% higher than 
the $11.4 million posted for the comparable 1989 period. Revenue for the three 
months ended Feb. 28 increased 12% to $1.1 billion from $970.4 million. 
</P>
<P>
For the first six months, net earnings rose 29% to $30.3 million from $23.4 
million for the comparable year-earlier period. Revenue increased 12% to $2.2 
billion from $1.9 billion. Emil P. Martini Jr., chairman and chief executive, 
said the prescription drug unit showed strong sales and earnings growth, while 
Commtron, the company's 80%-owned home entertainment distribution subsidiary, 
reported lower sales and operating earnings. 
</P>
</TEXT>
