<HEADLINE>
<P>
A SWEET CRITIC? 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Regarding Martin Bernheimer's review of Garrison Keillor at the Philharmonic 
pension fund benefit (March 14): Lordy, Lordy. 
</P>
<P>
Self-effacing, gentle and sweet are the only words that can apply. Not to 
Keillor's performance, but to the review. 
</P>
<P>
Bernheimer must have arisen from the right side of the sleeping apparatus 
(there are those who'd swear it's a Torquemadic contraption involving spikes, 
judging from the tone of some of his writings). 
</P>
<P>
A night of discovery and appreciation outside the more rarefied strata of 
traditionally "meaningful" musical efforts, from the Beckmesser-meister? "It 
was a lovely evening." It was a lovely review. 
</P>
<P>
MICHAEL McCONNOHIE, Burbank 
</P>
</TEXT>
