<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: OJAI; 
</P>
<P>
DEADLINE EXTENDED FOR ARTS ROSTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By THIA BELL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Artists, writers, actors and musicians still have an opportunity to be listed 
in the first city of Ojai Arts Roster. 
</P>
<P>
The deadline for free listings has been extended to March 22. 
</P>
<P>
More than 180 listings have been received, said Bert Collins of Ojai, a member 
of the city's Arts Advisory Committee. Committee members are compiling the free 
directory for distribution later this spring at City Hall, the Ojai Valley 
Chamber of Commerce, public libraries and businesses. 
</P>
<P>
There is no charge to artists to list a brief statement describing their 
medium, name and phone number. Addresses are optional, since the information 
will be made public. 
</P>
<P>
Committee member Bert Collins, an award-winning acrylic realist, will be 
accepting listings through next Thursday, the committee's next meeting, at Ojai 
City Hall, 401 S. Ventura St. It will begin at 6:30 p.m. Listings may also be 
given by phone at 646-6907. 
</P>
<P>
At the meeting, the city will select recipients of arts grants. Six applicants 
have applied for the $1,700 the city has budgeted for grants this year. 
</P>
<P>
Among programs seeking grants are art classes and the annual Ojai Music 
Festival, June 1-3, at Libbey Bowl. 
</P>
<P>
Other items on the panel's agenda are a proposal for funding from the Ventura 
County Art Alliance and the selection of artists for the Art in Public Places 
program. Under this program, paintings are selected for display in City Council 
chambers for six-week periods. THIA BELL 
</P>
</TEXT>
