WASHINGTON, D.C.; 
</P>
<P>
FIRM PLEADS GUILTY IN DOCUMENTS CASE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Grumman Corp. pleaded guilty in U.S. District Court in suburban Alexandria, 
Va., to illegally obtaining secret Air Force budget documents. 
</P>
<P>
The firm was fined $2.5 million. The company admitted obtaining secret Air 
Force program memorandums through a former employee, Harry Kotellos. Grumman is 
the fourth contractor since November to plead guilty to illegal trafficking of 
Pentagon documents. The others were Boeing Co., RCA Corp. and Hughes Aircraft. 
</P>
