<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE: HOUSTON'S WARE TO SKIP SENIOR YEAR, ENTER DRAFT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Quarterback Andre Ware, who set 25 NCAA records and won the Heisman Trophy in 
1989, announced Friday he will skip his final year at Houston and enter the NFL 
draft. 
</P>
<P>
Ware said he cherished his three years with the Cougars, but a variety of 
reasons led him to take advantage of the opportunity to play professionally. 
</P>
<P>
"We are here today, but we know not what tomorrow brings," Ware said, quoting 
his Sunday School teacher. "I live for today and I didn't want to come back (to 
school) and wonder 'what if I'd left?' and have that doubt in my mind." 
</P>
