<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: MAN TRIES TO RETRIEVE MODEL PLANE, FALLS 
OFF CLIFF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A man who climbed over the side of a cliff to retrieve a model plane Friday 
tumbled and fell about 225 feet and suffered minor injuries, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Ian Gittens, 32, of Redondo Beach, had gone to the seaside cliff in the 800 
block of Paseo del Mar to fly a remote-controlled model plane, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
The cliff is a popular spot for model airplane enthusiasts. 
</P>
<P>
About 1:20 p.m., Gittens climbed over the cliff's edge to retrieve the plane 
from a spot about 20 feet below the top when he slipped in the soft dirt, 
tumbling and falling about 225 feet, officials said. A Los Angeles County Fire 
Department crew found Gittens partially conscious and flew him to Harbor-UCLA 
Medical Center, where he was treated for extensive lacerations. 
</P>
