<HEADLINE>
<P>
STATE WILL HALVE ITS FARM WATER DELIVERIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SACRAMENTO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
State water officials said Friday they expect to cut by half the amount of 
water delivered this year to agricultural customers, citing low rainfall and 
dwindling storage as California faces a fourth year of drought. 
</P>
<P>
The Department of Water Resources said, however, that full water deliveries 
would continue to urban areas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
