<HEADLINE>
<P>
SWEDISH 'COMMANDOS' TO LAUNCH WAR ON RATS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
STOCKHOLM 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Authorities have declared war on rats in Stockholm, where experts say there are 
two rats for every human, the Svenska Dagbladet daily said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
The newspaper quoted officials as saying they expect it will take three years 
to bring the rats -- about 2 million of them -- under control. Starting next 
week, four "commando groups" will stalk the sewage system armed with rat 
poison. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
RATS; ANIMAL CONTROL; SWEDEN 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA031790-0131 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 191554 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
March 17, 1990, Saturday, Orange County Edition 
</P>
