<HEADLINE>
<P>
'JOE EGG' STAGING TO REPLACE 'YALLA BITCH' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JAN HERMAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SANTA ANA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Alternative Repertory Theatre will stage Peter Nichols' "A Day in the Death of 
Joe Egg" from April 27 to June 2. 
</P>
<P>
The 1967 black comedy about a British couple trying to cope with a severely 
handicapped child replaces Lorna Hill's "Yalla Bitch," which was dropped 
because of casting difficulties. 
</P>
<P>
Patricia L. Terry, artistic director of the storefront troupe, said Friday that 
rights to the play, which had been restricted, were granted this week by 
Nichols' agent. JAN HERMAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
ALTERNATIVE REPERTORY THEATRE; PLAYS; ARTS -- ORANGE COUNTY 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
</DOC>
